HDFS FILE MANAGEMENT USING HADOOP
(Without Java Program)
Step 1: Start Hadoop Services

Start HDFS:

start-dfs.sh

Start YARN:

start-yarn.sh

Verify Hadoop services:

jps

Expected Output:

NameNode
DataNode
SecondaryNameNode
ResourceManager
NodeManager
Jps
Step 2: Create a Local File

Create a text file:

nano sample.txt

Enter:

Hello Hadoop

Save and Exit:

CTRL + O
Enter
CTRL + X

Verify file:

cat sample.txt
Step 3: Create Directory in HDFS
hadoop fs -mkdir /input

Purpose:
Creates a directory named /input in HDFS.

Step 4: Upload File to HDFS
hadoop fs -put sample.txt /input/

Purpose:
Copies local file into HDFS.

Step 5: List Files in HDFS
hadoop fs -ls /input/

Expected Output:

sample.txt
Step 6: Read File from HDFS
hadoop fs -cat /input/sample.txt

Expected Output:

Hello Hadoop
Step 7: Download File from HDFS
hadoop fs -get /input/sample.txt downloaded.txt

Verify downloaded file:

cat downloaded.txt

Expected Output:

Hello Hadoop
Step 8: Delete File from HDFS
hadoop fs -rm /input/sample.txt

Purpose:
Deletes file from HDFS.

Step 9: Delete Directory from HDFS
hadoop fs -rm -r /input

Purpose:
Deletes directory and its contents.

MULTIPLE FILE OPERATIONS

Step 10: Create Multiple Files
echo "File 1 data" > file1.txt
echo "File 2 data" > file2.txt
echo "File 3 data" > file3.txt

Verify:

ls

Expected:

file1.txt
file2.txt
file3.txt
Step 11: Create HDFS Directory
hadoop fs -mkdir /multifiles
Step 12: Upload Multiple Files
hadoop fs -put file*.txt /multifiles/

Purpose:
Uploads all text files matching file*.txt.

Step 13: Verify Uploaded Files
hadoop fs -ls /multifiles

Expected:

file1.txt
file2.txt
file3.txt


Step 14: Read Individual Files
hadoop fs -cat /multifiles/file1.txt
hadoop fs -cat /multifiles/file2.txt
hadoop fs -cat /multifiles/file3.txt
Step 15: Read All Files Together
hadoop fs -cat /multifiles/*

Expected Output:

File 1 data
File 2 data
File 3 data


Step 16: Download Files
hadoop fs -get /multifiles/file1.txt
hadoop fs -get /multifiles/file2.txt
hadoop fs -get /multifiles/file3.txt


Step 17: Delete Files from HDFS
hadoop fs -rm /multifiles/file1.txt
hadoop fs -rm /multifiles/file2.txt
hadoop fs -rm /multifiles/file3.txt


Step 18: Delete HDFS Directory
hadoop fs -rm -r /multifiles
Step 19: Stop Hadoop Services

Stop YARN:

stop-yarn.sh

Stop HDFS:

stop-dfs.sh
